parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
often when the driver is not pressing the accelerator pedal. The acceleration can be rapid and uncontrollable
leading to accidents
crashes
and near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or hesitant acceleration can cause difficulties in merging, changing lanes, or accelerating from a stop, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or delays when accelerating from a stop
making it difficult to merge or change lanes. The acceleration may be slow or unpredictable
leading to frustration and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body or Electronic Control Unit (ECU) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body or ECU can cause sudden unintended acceleration, delayed or hesitant acceleration, or loss of power, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden unintended acceleration
delayed or hesitant acceleration
or loss of power
often accompanied by warning lights or error messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause the vehicle to speed out of control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the vehicle accelerates when the brake pedal is applied
the vehicle accelerates when the clutch pedal is applied
the vehicle accelerates on uneven road surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
the vehicle skids or slides when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal stuttering can cause the vehicle to jerk or stutter when braking, leading to loss of vehicle control or accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels like it's stuttering or jerking
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle jerks or stutters when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without warning
and may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause loss of power, hesitation, and stalling, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates
slips
or fails to engage
causing the vehicle to lurch or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to respond or are slow to engage
causing the vehicle to continue moving even when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic throttle control issues can cause unintended acceleration, hesitation, or stalling, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The throttle control system malfunctions
causing the vehicle to accelerate or hesitate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag failure can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbags fail to deploy in a crash
or deploy unnecessarily.
